    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112G64/2./2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Minister of Ecuador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                    Department has been advised by the American Minister to Ecuador that the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs has stated to him the intention of the President of
                    Ecuador to present for the consideration of the Secretary of State, through the
                    Ecuadorian Legation, the question of permitting Goo Kwai, an American citizen of
                    Chinese birth, to enter Ecuador for a visit to relatives.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to request, therefore, that you inform the Department whether
                    you have received any instructions from your Government to take up this matter
                    with the Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
